OL,3,CPolice chiefs to be questioned about
OL,4,Casylum centre tensions
OL,6,FHer comments follow a move by
OL,7,Fcampaigners who plan to fight the
OL,8,Fplans for the camp and have raised
OL,9,Fthousands of pounds from local people
OL,10,Fto mount a legal challenge.
OL,12,FThey believe they can win a judicial
OL,13,Freview at the High Court - arguing
OL,14,Fthat the Home Office has breached
OL,15,Fplanning procedures in its drive to
OL,16,Fhave the 600-place camp up and running
OL,17,Fby the end of the month.
